    "instruction": "Load trace.csv. Restrict analysis to the candidate services: ts-auth-service, ts-order-service, ts-route-service, ts-train-service, ts-travel-service. For each (cmdb_id, trace_name) pair across the full trace.csv compute the global P95 of 'value' (no time filtering). Then filter trace.csv to the incident window 2024-01-24 17:13:24 to 2024-01-24 17:43:24 UTC. For each (cmdb_id, trace_name) in that window, find rows where value >= global P95. Aggregate anomalies to one row per (cmdb_id, trace_name) with columns: cmdb_id, trace_name, total_points_in_window, count_anom_points, first_anom_timestamp (earliest anomaly ts in window, UTC), max_value_in_window, global_p95, severity = max_value_in_window / global_p95. Return the aggregated rows (top 20) sorted by severity descending. If no anomalies are found for these candidates, return an explicit empty/none result message."
