    "analysis": "Executor's trace analysis (using full-series global P95s, then filtering to the incident window) found the strongest trace anomalies on ts-order-service (notably trace.from_ts-preserve-service.duration_mean and duration_p95 at 17:22:00 UTC, severity ~2.2 and ~1.4). Other candidate services (ts-auth-service, ts-route-service, ts-travel-service, ts-train-service) showed moderate trace anomalies (several duration and row_count spikes), and ts-train-service had a metric-level disk I/O spike earlier (17:16:00 UTC) with high severity from the previous metric analysis. At this point we have two strong signals: (A) ts-train-service diskio high-severity anomaly at 17:16 UTC (metrics), and (B) ts-order-service latency and row_count anomalies around 17:19–17:22 UTC (traces). According to the diagnosis workflow, we must compare metric anomalies for the allowed candidate services, examine timing and severity, then use logs to confirm operation errors or traffic surges that help localize the root cause component and reason.",
